erein, means a regulation, standard, statement of policy, or interpretation of general application and future effect. Additionally, the West Virginia Department of Education shall propose rules for legislative approval pursuant to §29A-3-1 et seq. of this code, and rulemaking by the department shall not be implemented until the legislative rules have been approved by the Legislature.NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to bring the West Virginia Department of Education (WVDE) under rulemaking review of the Legislature. Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: